2. NVIDIA CUDA / cuDNN / cuBLAS runtime dependencies (not bundled)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Vokra does not bundle or redistribute any NVIDIA runtime component
(CUDA runtime / cudart, cuDNN, cuBLAS). When the CUDA backend is enabled,
Vokra detects a system-installed CUDA at runtime via dynamic loading
(e.g. dlopen("libcuda.so") on Linux, LoadLibrary("nvcuda.dll") on Windows).
Installing NVIDIA components and accepting the corresponding NVIDIA EULAs
is the responsibility of the end user or integrating developer. cuDNN is
never a hard requirement of Vokra. The full EULA-compliance strategy (the
5 points: no bundling, runtime detection, explicit version probe, cuDNN
optional, this record) is documented in third_party/NVIDIA-EULA.md, which
is the authoritative reference for the vokra-backend-cuda crate.

Timing note: the CUDA backend is planned for the v0.5-v1.0 releases (M2-03).
The M2-03 foundation slice (crates/vokra-backend-cuda) lands the driver
probe and an FP32 GEMM via raw CUDA Driver API + NVRTC loaded by dlopen,
with NO cudarc/cust/rustacuda binding crate and no bundled CUDA runtime.

