7. SpeexDSP echo canceller (Rust port of mdf.c for the `aec` operator)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Vokra's acoustic echo cancellation operator (crates/vokra-ops/src/aec.rs,
M4-03 / FR-OP-60) is a from-scratch Rust port — a derivative work, not a
clean-room reimplementation — of the SpeexDSP echo canceller
(libspeexdsp/mdf.c, the MDF/AUMDF adaptive filter with the Valin 2007
variable learning rate), Copyright (C) 2003-2008 Jean-Marc Valin,
distributed under the 3-clause BSD license as part of SpeexDSP
(Copyright 2002-2008 Xiph.org Foundation and contributors).

  Source: https://github.com/xiph/speexdsp
          (pinned commit 7a158783df74efe7c2d1c6ee8363c1e695c71226)
  License: 3-clause BSD — full text reproduced in
          crates/vokra-ops/THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES/speexdsp-LICENSE.txt

No SpeexDSP C source is bundled, compiled, or linked into any Vokra
artifact (NFR-DS-02 zero-dependency); the port is pure Rust. The upstream
code is only executed offline by the developer-side parity tool
(tools/parity/aec_dump.py) to produce the committed reference fixtures
under tests/parity/aec/. The far-end reference queue
(crates/vokra-core/src/stream/aec_ref.rs) is an original Vokra design and
not derived from SpeexDSP.

