10. Japanese G2P chain (Open JTalk lineage) — BSD-3-Clause notices
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Vokra's Japanese text-to-speech front-end resolves grapheme-to-phoneme
through `jpreprocess`, a Rust reimplementation of Open JTalk that bundles
the NAIST Japanese Dictionary. It is used by the excluded workspace
`integrations/vokra-piper-g2p`, which drives plain-Japanese synthesis for
the piper-plus voices.

That lineage is permissively licensed end to end -- there is no GPL
obligation anywhere in it, because the HTS Working Group elected the BSD
arm of MeCab's disjunctive tri-license upstream. Vokra makes the same
election explicitly, and records it here so an auditor does not have to
infer which branch was taken:

  **Vokra elects the BSD-3-Clause arm of the MeCab tri-license
  (GPL-2.0 / LGPL-2.1 / BSD-3-Clause).**

BSD-3-Clause clause 2 requires that a *binary* redistribution reproduce the
copyright notice and conditions. Vokra ships binaries, so these notices are
carried here rather than left to the upstream packaging -- which does not
discharge the obligation on our behalf.

